parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause vibrations, noise, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the control arm bushings can cause uneven tire wear, vibrations, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of functionality, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates without pressing the pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the power steering hose can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering hose is leaking fluid
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
grinding noise from the steering column
and the power steering pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front end components can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The front tires are pointing in opposite directions
the passenger side outer tie rod end separates from the steering knuckle
and the front hub assembly needs to be replaced.
